<TITLE> New hearing set for Aug 21 grenade case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, August 3 (bdnews24.com)A Dhaka court on Sunday set Aug 31 as the next date for charge framing proceedings in a case involving the Aug 21, 2004, grenade attack. Hearing on charge framing in the August 21 grenade attack and murder case was scheduled to be held Sunday. But in view of a defence petition for more time, Dhaka metropolitan additional sessions sudge Md KM Rasheduzzaman Raja set the new hearing date. However, the court was prompted to make it clear that no more time would be allowed in this respect. Mohammad Ali, lawyer of the accused Abdus Salam Pintu told the court: "The authorities have not provided the certified copies of the charge sheet, seizure lists and other relevant papers so far, which we applied for." "This is why we are not adequately prepared and have asked for additional time." Lawyers of other accused in the case Hossain Ahmed Tamim, Md Abul Kalam Azad and Jahangir Alam also cited similar reasons for requesting more time. Public prosecutor Ehsanul Haque Shamaji voiced no objection to the defence lawyers' request, saying: "The defence has the right to be provided with the certified copies of the case documents and therefore they might expect their time plea to be granted." As bail petitions for accused Abdus Salam Pintu, Maulana Abu Taher, Maulana Abu Sayeed, Arif Hasan Shuman, Abul Kalam Azad and Jahangir Alam were also submitted to the court Sunday, the court also set Aug 31 for their bail hearings. All the 13 accused arrested in the caseformer deputy education minister Abdus Salam Pintu and Harkatul Jihad leaders Mufti Abdul Hannan, Maulana Abu Taher, Maulana Abu Sayeed, Md Abul Kalam Azad, Jahangir Alam, Hossain Ahmed Tamim and Shahadat Ullah Jewel, among otherswere present in court Sunday. Charges were pressed in the case on June 11. bdnews
